There is no centralized system for abortion services in Mongolia. Abortion services are dispensed and regulated at the local level by the MOH. Abortion services can be accessed through the public sector or the private sector. Whereas Mongolia’s public sector provides free abortion services, private providers charge for abortion services. Sex ratio at birth imbalance Many countries have taken a conservative approach to address gender imbalance, while many countries have considered statutory measures to regulate sex-neutral reproductive technology (Amatuzzi, 2006). In 2018, CHDC’s research indicated that the national sex ratio at birth (SRB) was 1.12, which is lower than most countries in the Asia Pacific region (IAGI, 2017); Thus, the sex ratio imbalance is the gender disparity at birth resulting from sex-selective abortion and selective at-birth termination of pregnancy as well as from maternal sexual selection, a consequence of infanticide, and/or natural selection (Wang, 2006). Malaysia, for example, has implemented stringent measures to reduce gender imbalance since 1985.
